<br>
A very involved tradeskiller told me and others he had stumbled across a way to duplicate things that stack, and tested it on something silly like food, and found it did reproduce.  He reported it, and would say no more about it.  Not even though I was dying of curiousity.  Curiousity is dangerous that way.  My conscience would never allow me to actually exploit such a bug (the closest I ever came was making cheese. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) but I admit I was dying to know how.  Just so I could say I did.  I don't know.  I'm glad I didn't know now, and still don't.  But the important point is, this was right after the bazaar became active.  How lnog ago was that?  A couple of months?<br>
<br>
I have no way of knowing if the bug is the same, but this could have been going on for ages with no one noticing.  God, the safest way to do it wouild be to duplicate stack after stack of rubies and sell them back to the vendor who natually stocks them.  Then there would be no suspecious influx of rare drops.  How knows, maybe people were doing that for a long long time before the exploit found its way into the hands of someone stupider?  It's possible.<br>
<br>
I don't have much of a point, except kudos to the fellow who first found the dupe and did nothing with it.  I'm sure he did nothing because I know how hard he's worked to fund his tradeskilling.  And special kudoes for telling no one else about it (if he didn't tell me, or people we both know, he didn't tell anyone).  And to everyone else...yeah, this sucks a lot.  But knowing things like this happen...you just can't let it ruin everything for you.  Get on with the game, and remember that earning what you have really is more fun.  And fun is still the point.<br>
<br>
